This paper is primarily focused on image processing and computer vision, which suggests that it is likely to belong to the cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition) sub-category. Additionally, the use of deep neural networks and dynamic programming suggests that it may also belong to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-categories. The focus on computational complexity and hardware performance suggests that it may also belong to the cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) sub-category. Finally, the use of max-pooling layers suggests that it may also belong to the cs.MM (Multimedia) sub-category.
